Teva Pharmaceuticals, the creators of Plan B (the &quot;morning-after pill&quot;) has repeatedly asked the FDA to remove its warning label that the drug &quot;may inhibit implantation by altering the endometrium [the inside lining of the uterus].&quot;

In other words, it can create a bad uterus for implantation to occur, thus, causing miscarry or abortion.

